#### 5. Session Expiry Warning
**Impact:** High User Experience Enhancement

**Changes:**
- Client-side session monitoring
- Modal warning 5 minutes before expiry
- Live countdown timer
- Option to continue or logout
- Activity-based timer reset

**Files Modified:**
- `views/layouts/main.ejs`
  - Added data attributes for session config
  - `data-authenticated` flag
  - `data-session-max-age` value
  - Lines added: ~1 line modified

- `public/js/main.js`
  - Added session expiry warning system (~130 lines)
  - `showSessionWarning()` function
  - `scheduleSessionWarning()` function
  - `resetSessionTimer()` function
  - Activity event listeners
  - Bootstrap modal creation
  - Countdown timer implementation
  - Lines added: ~135 lines

**Technical Implementation:**
```javascript
const SESSION_MAX_AGE = 86400000; // 24 hours
const WARNING_TIME = 5 * 60 * 1000; // 5 minutes
const TIME_UNTIL_WARNING = SESSION_MAX_AGE - WARNING_TIME;

// Show warning after 23 hours 55 minutes
setTimeout(showSessionWarning, TIME_UNTIL_WARNING);
```

**Activity Tracking:**
- Monitors: mousedown, keypress, scroll, click
- Resets timer only if >1 minute since last activity
- Prevents excessive API calls

**User Interface:**
- Bootstrap modal with warning styling
- Live countdown: "5:00" → "4:59" → "4:58" ...
- Two action buttons: "Continue Session" | "Logout Now"

---

#### 6. Password Reset Support
**Impact:** High User Experience & Security Enhancement

**Changes:**
- Complete password reset flow
- Secure token-based system
- Email integration placeholder
- Token expiration mechanism
- Account unlock on successful reset

**Files Created:**
- `views/auth/forgot-password.ejs`
  - Form to request password reset
  - Email input field
  - Link back to login
  - Lines: ~50 lines

- `views/auth/reset-password.ejs`
  - Form to enter new password
  - Token validation display
  - Password confirmation
  - Lines: ~80 lines

**Files Modified:**
- `models/User.js`
  - Added `resetPasswordToken` (String, default: null)
  - Added `resetPasswordExpires` (Date, default: null)
  - Added `createPasswordResetToken()` instance method
  - Lines added: ~25 lines

- `controllers/authController.js`
  - Added `renderForgotPassword()` - GET /forgot-password
  - Added `forgotPassword()` - POST /forgot-password
  - Added `renderResetPassword()` - GET /reset-password/:token
  - Added `resetPassword()` - POST /reset-password/:token
  - Added crypto import for token hashing
  - Lines added: ~190 lines

- `routes/authRoutes.js`
  - Added 4 new routes for password reset
  - Lines added: ~5 lines

- `views/auth/login.ejs`
  - Added "Forgot your password?" link
  - Added success message display support
  - Lines added: ~10 lines

**Security Features:**
- Tokens are cryptographically hashed (SHA-256)
- 1-hour token expiration
- Generic success messages (prevent email enumeration)
- Validates password strength on reset
- Checks password reuse
- Clears failed login attempts
- Unlocks account automatically

**Token Generation Algorithm:**
```javascript
const resetToken = crypto.randomBytes(32).toString('hex');
this.resetPasswordToken = crypto
    .createHash('sha256')
    .update(resetToken)
    .digest('hex');
this.resetPasswordExpires = Date.now() + 60 * 60 * 1000;
return resetToken; // Unhashed for email link
```

**Production Note:**
Currently logs token to console. Requires email service integration:
```javascript
// TODO: Replace with nodemailer
console.log('Reset URL:', `http://localhost:3000/reset-password/${resetToken}`);
```

**Database Schema Changes:**
```javascript
resetPasswordToken: { type: String, default: null },
resetPasswordExpires: { type: Date, default: null }
```

