---

### Lessons Learned

**What Went Well:**
- Modular implementation allowed incremental testing
- Pre-save hooks in Mongoose simplified password history
- Bootstrap modals worked perfectly for session warning
- Clear separation of concerns (controller/service/view)

**Challenges Encountered:**
- Whitespace issues in EJS template editing
- Session timer coordination with server-side expiry
- Balance between security and user experience

**Best Practices Applied:**
- Cryptographic token hashing (not storing raw tokens)
- Generic error messages (prevent user enumeration)
- Progressive disclosure (warnings before lockout)
- Sensible defaults (all new fields have default values)
- Comprehensive error handling throughout

